question.title: Will TRMB's market close price on 2026-02-14 be higher than its market close price on 2026-02-07?
question.description:
Trimble Inc. is a company that is listed on the S&P 500 index. It's ticker is TRMB. It's last close price as of the creation of this question (2026-02-01 03:34:42) is 67.6. You can find more information about Trimble Inc. at https://finance.yahoo.com/quote/TRMB

Trimble Inc. provides technology solutions that enable professionals and field mobile workers to enhance or transform their work processes in North America, Europe, the Asia Pacific, and internationally. The company offers architecture design, engineering, construction, and owner software products. It also offers field-based data collection systems and field software, and real-time communications systems, as well as back-office software for data processing, modeling, monitoring, reporting, and analysis; software for planning, data processing and editing, quality control, 3D modeling, intelligent data analysis and AI-based feature extraction, deformation monitoring, project reporting, and data export; field and office software for project design and visualization; office-based products, such as software for 3D design and data sharing; systems to guide and control construction equipment; and software to facilitate the management of the construction process. In addition, it offers positioning services, such as VRSNow; CenterPoint RTX; FieldPoint RTX; Rangepoint RTX; ViewPoint RTX; Trimble xFill; and OmniSTAR (HP, XP, G2, and VBS) services. Further, it offers transportation management system that automates business processes for shippers, carriers, and intermediaries, as well as truck routing, mileage, mapping, and voice navigation solutions; and transporeon solutions that offers freight sourcing and procurement, such as dock and yard management, and freight auditing. It serves architecture, engineering, construction, design, asset management, operations, and maintenance; private, commercial, and government; and shippers, carriers, and intermediaries customers. It sells its technology solutions directly to its customers in central Illinois, eastern Iowa, and northeast Missouri. The company was formerly known as Trimble Navigation Limited and changed its name to Trimble Inc. in October 2016. Trimble Inc. was founded in 1978 and is headquartered in Westminster, Colorado.
